&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Order to Cash (O2C) Operations / Order Management Specialist (12-month contract)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Scandit WARSAW&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Imagine the what. Build the how.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Scandit gives people superpowers. Whether enabling delivery drivers to make quicker deliveries, matching a patient with their medication, or allowing retailers to make store operations more efficient, our technology automates workflows. It provides actionable insights to help businesses in a variety of industries. Join us as we continue to expand, grow, innovate, and help take Scandit to the next level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Scandit is looking for an &lt;strong&gt;Order to Cash Specialist&lt;/strong&gt; to join the Order to Cash team. This is a hands-on operational role requiring demonstrated experience in order management within a SaaS environment, with direct ownership of end-to-end order-to-cash processes, and cross-functional coordination across Sales, Finance, and Operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is open to candidates with a minimum of &lt;strong&gt;5 years&lt;/strong&gt; of relevant experience in order management or a closely related order-to-cash function, ideally within a SaaS or subscription-based business. Candidates with strong Salesforce proficiency and practical knowledge of AI tools, including Claude or equivalent, to support order entry, data quality, and workflow efficiency are strongly preferred.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Order Management and Financial System Operations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own end-to-end order entry and validation across Salesforce and NetSuite, ensuring accuracy, completeness, and compliance with booking policies and data quality standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage complex order types including amendments, co-terms, upgrades, and multi-element arrangements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead customer cycle management and dispute resolution&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and enforce data integrity standards across CRM and ERP systems; identify and remediate data quality issues proactively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee licence key management and ensure timely and accurate provisioning aligned to contract terms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a point of contact for order-related queries from Sales, Deal Desk, and Finance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Automation, Process Improvement, and AI Tooling&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply AI tools — including Claude and similar platforms — to accelerate order entry, data validation, draft communications, and process documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead or co-lead automation initiatives within the O2C function; evaluate, test, and implement tooling to reduce manual effort&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify process inefficiencies and drive continuous improvement across the order-to-cash cycle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document current-state and future-state processes; maintain operational runbooks and training materials&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support system configuration and data clean-up projects in Salesforce, including deduplication and record hygiene&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-functional Coordination and Reporting&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Sales, Deal Desk, Legal, and Revenue Ops to resolve complex order scenarios, billing holds, and contract disputes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support month-end and quarter-end close by ensuring all bookings are processed, reconciled, and traceable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with audit requirements by maintaining complete and accurate financial records&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to reporting and operational metrics for the O2C function; flag trends and escalate risks proactively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
